<br>
See <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :2cent --><img src=http://www.spacespider.net/emo/twocents.gif ALT=":2cent"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I left my main character when I came to FV, the druid that I had spent countless hours building on Brell, equipping her in what at the time was uber equipment, raising her levels, and forging friendships and ongoing storylines.<br>
<br>
Everything she has, with the exception of one item I was gifted with, was earned by me.<br>
<br>
Ssakas is now my 11th (I believe) character on FV, and finally, one that I have stuck with.  I did not start over from scratch each time I rerolled, althought there are some who believe I should have.  Why?  Because I earned everything Ssakas uses, either by buying it, looting it, or gaining it through my guild.  Ssakas didn't earn everything, but *I* earned everything on this server.<br>
<br>
This, in my opinion, is the difference.  It is why even those of us who think twinking is completely acceptable can be against the transfer of items between servers.<br>
<br>
Even if Ssakas didn't earn it all, it was still all earned on this server.<br>
<br>
But if I decided that I really want the 30k or so worth of items my druid has that are wasting away untouched over on Brell, items that I *willingly* gave up to move here, then I am bringing items and plat that were not earned on FV into the equation.<br>
<br>
Now personally, here comes my two differnet mindsets on the topic.<br>
<br>
If you traded the items/plat to a character on your old server, for items/plat that originated on this server, I can not find any fault with that.  You are not bringing anything new into the economy, the items were already here.  The problem is finding someone you can trust who wants to trade.  Good luck with that.  I believe trades like that are against the EULA (not sure) and I am sure that SOE wouldn't be there to help if you got ripped off.<br>
<br>
I mean really though, I'm not going to be a hypocrite.  If someone offered me 10-15K here for the items on a character I will never play again on brell, and I could trust the person, I would do it.  I probably wouldn't annouce it from the highest mountaintop, but I would still do it.<br>
<br>
Now, for the other side of my argument....<br>
<br>
I am against bringing items/plat that originated on other servers to FV.  Why, because it messes up our economy, the same way a elemental capable guild transfering over would screw up our guild status.  Injecting things from different servers into our server WILL change our server.  This is why legends smuggling causes such an outcry here, and why so many are against letting transfers, even naked, onto our server.<br>
<br>
I would never take sylvania to legends, so I could smuggle that 30 k or so over here.<br>
<br>
Yes, I earned all her stuff.  But I didn't earn it here.  And even though 30k being brought onto the server wouldn't change anything, 100 people with the same idea doing the same thing would.<br>
<br>
*shrugs*<br>
<br>
Ok, that's about 5 and a half coppers.<br>
<br>
